{
  "stem": "17821.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 167.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we moved on the street called Impasse des Charmilles, which was not very elegant.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we couldn't afford better.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then eventually, we moved out into a house, which was nicer in the suburbs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And our baby was born-- our little girl was born.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then we moved back in-- after a while into Paris and lived again in, in Paris.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'29-- December, 1929.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Annie.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, absolutely.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was-- the-- only in 1938, I noticed newspapers being sold on the streets had some kind of a heading which was anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the first time I'd seen it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was very impolite to talk to people about their religion.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People just didn't talk about one another's religion.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You didn't know what religion people were.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they had a very rude expression.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If somebody asked what your religion was, they would say, [SPEAKING FRENCH], which means, and your wife, does she deceive you?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the French.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What, what was it like being married to a foreigner, given all of the feeling toward foreigners at that time?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It didn't seem to matter, so long as he had a job, which wasn't often.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had friends there among the French.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And did we have Jewish friends?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we have some Jewish friends and some non.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody bothered about religion.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I did secretarial work.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Having a French degree wasn't much use to get a job in France.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was the wrong language.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had their French.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I went, and I learned shorthand and typing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I got jobs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the main job I got was with Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The-- that was their main office in France.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
